1. Mechanic spec (heart → employee system)

1.1. Core entities

• Player• Fields: player_id, tiktok_account_id, xbox_gamertag, heart_pool, employee_tokens, settings_kid_mode, settings_notifications

• HeartEvent• Fields: event_id, player_id, source (like / comment / gift / effect), heart_type (❤️, 💖, etc.), timestamp, weight

• HeartPool• Fields: player_id, total_hearts, daily_hearts, lifetime_hearts, last_reset_at

• EmployeeToken• Fields: token_id, player_id, tier (standard / specialist / guardian), source (community_hearts), created_at, redeemed (bool)

• Employee• Fields: employee_id, player_id, role, rarity, tier, origin_ritual (text), created_at



---

1.2. Core loop

1. TikTok interaction happens (like, heart emoji, gift, etc.).
2. System creates a HeartEvent with a weight based on type.
3. HeartEvent increments HeartPool for that player.
4. When thresholds are crossed, system mints EmployeeTokens.
5. Player visits “Ceremony Screen” in game to redeem tokens.
6. A ritual animation plays → Employee is generated and added to roster.


---

1.3. Heart weighting

• Like: weight = 1
• Heart emoji in comment: weight = 2
• Heart gift / sticker: weight = 3–5 (configurable)
• Heart effect / filter usage: weight = 2


Weights are tunable via config, not hard‑coded.

---

1.4. Thresholds (example defaults)

• 50 weighted hearts → 1 Standard Employee Token
• 250 weighted hearts → 1 Specialist Token
• 1,000 weighted hearts → 1 Guardian Token


Tokens stack; thresholds are cumulative, not “spend and reset.”

---

1.5. Token → employee generation

• Standard Token• Roles: clerk, mechanic, courier, assistant
• Rarity: common/uncommon

• Specialist Token• Roles: engineer, trainer, merchant, scout
• Rarity: uncommon/rare

• Guardian Token• Roles: ceremonial steward, guardian, overseer
• Rarity: rare/legendary



Generation uses:

• Seed: player_id + token_id + timestamp
• Tables: role table, rarity table, cosmetic variants


