7. Kid‑safe guardrails

7.1. Design principles

• No gambling metaphors• No loot boxes, spinning wheels, or random “pull” animations.

• No pay‑to‑win• Employees are helpers, not overpowering advantages.

• No pressure language• Avoid: “Hurry!”, “Don’t miss out!”, “You need hearts to progress.”

• No direct ask to viewers• The game never says: “Tell your friends to send hearts.”



---

7.2. Parental / guardian controls

• Kid Mode toggle (per account):• Effects:• Hides heart counts.
• Shows only “You received help from your community” without numbers.
• Limits frequency of ceremonies (e.g., max 1 per day).
• Disables any references to TikTok or external platforms in‑game UI.


• Settings examples:• “Show heart numbers”: On/Off
• “Show community source (TikTok)”: On/Off
• “Limit ceremonies per day”: 1 / 3 / Unlimited



---

7.3. Communication tone

• Always:• “Hearts are a way people say thank you.”
• “You can enjoy the game fully without any hearts.”

• Never:• “You need more hearts.”
• “Ask your friends to send hearts.”
• “Spend to get more hearts.”



